def get_models_depth():
    models = dict()
    for i in range(1,6, 1):
        base = DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=i)
        models[str(i)] = AdaBoostClassifier(base_estimator=base, n_estimators=coarse_n, 
                                            learning_rate=coarse_learn, random_state=22)
    return models

def get_models_trees():
    models = dict()
    n_trees = [30, 50, 80, 100]
    for n in n_trees:
        models[str(n)] = AdaBoostClassifier(base_estimator = DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=coarse_depth), 
                                            n_estimators=n, learning_rate = coarse_learn, random_state=22)
    return models

def get_models_learning():
    models = dict()
    for i in [0.001, 0.01, 0.1, 1]:
        key = '%.4f' % i
        models[key] = AdaBoostClassifier(base_estimator = DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=coarse_depth), 
                                         learning_rate=i, n_estimators=coarse_n, random_state=22)
    return models

def evaluate_model(model, X, y):
    cv = KFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=1)
    scores = cross_val_score(model, X, y, scoring='roc_auc', cv=cv, n_jobs=-1)
    return scores

#Evaluate depth
models = get_models_depth()
results, names = list(), list()
for name, model in models.items():
    scores = evaluate_model(model, X_train_sample, y_train_sample)
    results.append(scores)
    names.append(name)

plt.figure(figsize=(5, 5))
plt.boxplot(results, labels=names, showmeans=True)
plt.ylabel('ROC-AUC',fontsize=15)
plt.xlabel('Depth of each tree',fontsize=15)
plt.axvline(x = names.index(str(coarse_depth))+1, color = 'red')

import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")
threshold_hyperparam_vals = np.arange(0.49, 0.51, 0.001)
accuracy_iter = pd.DataFrame(columns = {'threshold', 'precision', 'recall', 'n_estimators', 'max_depth', 'learning_rate', 'roc_auc', 'f1'})
iter_number = 0

#Defining Parameter grid
grid = dict()
grid['n_estimators'] = [30, 50, 80]
grid['learning_rate'] = [0.1, 1]
grid['base_estimator'] = [DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=1), DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=2)]

for n in grid['n_estimators']:
    for rate in grid['learning_rate']:
        for est in grid['base_estimator']:
            model_cool = AdaBoostClassifier(random_state=1,
                                                  n_estimators = n, 
                                                  base_estimator = est, 
                                                  learning_rate = rate)
                        
            predicted_probability = cross_val_predict(model_cool, X_train, 
                                                      y_train, cv = 2, method = 'predict_proba', n_jobs = -1)
                    
            roc_auc = roc_auc_score(y_train, predicted_probability[:,1])

            for threshold_prob in threshold_hyperparam_vals:
                predicted_class = predicted_probability[:,1] > threshold_prob
                predicted_class = predicted_class.astype(int)

                #Computing the accuracy
                precision = precision_score(y_train, predicted_class)*100
                recall = recall_score(y_train, predicted_class)*100
                f1 = f1_score(y_train, predicted_class)*100
                accuracy_iter.loc[iter_number, 'n_estimators'] = n
                accuracy_iter.loc[iter_number, 'base_estimator'] = est
                accuracy_iter.loc[iter_number, 'learning_rate'] = rate
                accuracy_iter.loc[iter_number, 'precision'] = precision
                accuracy_iter.loc[iter_number, 'recall'] = recall
                accuracy_iter.loc[iter_number, 'f1'] = f1
                accuracy_iter.loc[iter_number, 'roc_auc'] = roc_auc
                accuracy_iter.loc[iter_number, 'threshold'] = threshold_prob
                

                iter_number = iter_number + 1
best_model = accuracy_iter.loc[accuracy_iter.loc[:, "roc_auc"] == accuracy_iter.loc[:, "roc_auc"].max()]
best_model = accuracy_iter.loc[accuracy_iter.loc[:, "f1"] == accuracy_iter.loc[:, "f1"].max(), :]

def plot_precision_recall_vs_threshold(precisions, recalls, thresholds):
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))
    plt.title("Precision and Recall Scores as a function of the decision threshold")
    plt.plot(thresholds, precisions[:-1], "b--", label="Precision")
    plt.plot(thresholds, recalls[:-1], "g-", label="Recall")
    plt.plot(thresholds, precisions[:-1], "o", color = 'blue')
    plt.plot(thresholds, recalls[:-1], "o", color = 'green')
    plt.ylabel("Score")
    plt.xlabel("Decision Threshold")
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    plt.legend()
plot_precision_recall_vs_threshold(p, r, thresholds)

from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve


def plot_roc_curve(fpr, tpr, label=None):
    
    plt.plot(fpr, tpr, linewidth=2, label=label)
    plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], "k--")
    plt.axis([0, 1, 0, 1])
    plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
    plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
    plt.title('ROC Curve')

fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_test, y_pred_proba)
plt.figure(figsize= (7, 5))
plot_roc_curve(fpr, tpr)
